üöÄüêü Spacefish



A Fish Shell prompt for Astronauts.

Spacefish is a Fish Shell port of Spaceship; the minimalistic, powerful and extremely customizable Zsh prompt. It combines everything you may need for convenient work, without unnecessary complications, like a real spacefish.
Features

Prompt character turns red if the last command exits with non-zero code.
Execution time of the last command if it exceeds 5 seconds.
Current Git branch and rich repo status:
? ‚Äî untracked changes;
+ ‚Äî uncommitted changes in the index;
! ‚Äî unstaged changes;
¬ª ‚Äî renamed files;
‚úò ‚Äî deleted files;
$ ‚Äî stashed changes;
= ‚Äî unmerged changes;
‚á° ‚Äî ahead of remote branch;
‚á£ ‚Äî behind of remote branch;
‚áï ‚Äî diverged chages.


Current battery level and status:
‚á° - charging;
‚á£ - discharging;
‚Ä¢ - fully charged.



Upcoming features

Displaying hostname/username
Indicator if user is root
Indicator for jobs in the background (‚ú¶).
Current Node.js version, through nvm/nodenv/n (‚¨¢).
Current Ruby version, through rvm/rbenv/chruby (üíé).
Current Python pyenv (üêç).
Package version, if there's is a package in current directory (üì¶).
Optional exit-code of last command.
Optional time stamps 12/24hr in format.

Want more features? Please, open an issue or send pull request.
Preview

  


Requirements
To get spacefish working correctly you will need:

fish (v2.7.0 or newer)
Powerline Font must be installed and enabled in your terminal.

Installation
Fisherman
$ fisher spacefish

Oh My Fish!
$ omf install spacefish

Customization
Spacefish works well out of the box, but you can customize almost everything if you want.

Options ‚Äî Tweak section's behavior with tons of options.

You have the ability to customize or disable specific elements of Spacefish. All options must be overridden in your config.fish.

docs/Options.html.body:
Options
You have ability to customize or disable specific elements of Spacefish. All options must be overridden in your config.fish.
Colors for sections can be basic colors or color codes.
Note: the symbol ¬∑ in this document represents a regular space character  , it is used to clearly indicate when an option default value starts or ends with a space.
Order
You can specify the order of prompt section using SPACEFISH_PROMPT_ORDER option. Use Zsh array syntax to define your own prompt order.
The order also defines which sections that Spacefish loads. If you're struggling with slow prompt, you can just omit the sections that you don't use, and they won't be loaded.
The default order is:
    set SPACEFISH_PROMPT_ORDER dir git exec_time line_sep battery char

Prompt

Meaning
